Wakilan jihohi 18 da gundumomi sun gabatar da wata takarda a ranar Juma'a a Washington don tallafawa 'yan gudun hijira da ke kalubalanci dokar, in ji NBC News.
An dai bayyana cikakken sunayen masu karar Grace v. Grace a cikin karar da kungiyar kare hakkin jama'a ta American Civil Liberties Union ta shigar a watan Agusta kan dokar tarayya ba a bayyana ba.
Ya ce abokin aikinsa "da dansa, wanda shi ma ɗan kungiyar 'yan daba ne", sun yi masa ba'a, amma jami'an Amurka sun ki amincewa da neman mafaka a ranar 20 ga Yuli.
An kama shi a Texas.
Lauyoyin jihohi da ke goyon bayan Grace sun bayyana El Salvador, Honduras, da Guatemala, wadanda ke samar da mafi yawan 'yan gudun hijira zuwa Amurka, a matsayin kasashen da ke fuskantar babbar matsalar' yan bindiga da kuma tashin hankali na cikin gida.
Sabuwar dokar ta saba wa dokar da Kwamitin da ke da alhakin shige da fice na Amurka ya yanke a shekarar 2014 wanda ya ba wa 'yan gudun hijira damar neman mafaka.
Babban Lauyan District of Columbia, Karl Racine ya ce a cikin wata sanarwa a ranar Juma'a cewa wannan sabuwar manufar "ta yi watsi da dokokin jihohi, na tarayya, da na kasa da kasa da suka kasance shekaru da yawa".
"Dokar tarayya ta ce dole ne a yanke hukunci kan duk wani neman mafaka bisa ga wasu hujjoji da kuma yanayi da suka shafi wannan neman, kuma irin wannan haramcin ya sabawa ka'ida", in ji aminiyar kotun.
